observations.recommendation:
a. Direct the Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer to continue the conduct of the regular reconciliation of the cash accounts balances, and exert maximum effort in tracing and verifying the account;
b. Require the Municipal Accountant to revert back to cash the amount corresponding to unreleased checks as of end of the year; and
c. Send written notice to the payees informing them about the stale check for cancellation or replacement in accordance with Section 59 of Chapter III, Volume I of Manual on the New Government Accounting Systems for Local Government Units.

a. Ensure that the 30% Quick Response Fund should only be used during a state of calamity duly declared by the Local Sanggunian;
b. Ensure strict control procedures in the disbursement of the funds to ensure that it is utilized only for its intended purpose; and
c. Regularly submit the monthly Reports on Sources and Utilization of LDRRM Fund to COA and other offices, in accordance with Sections 5.1.5 and 5.1.6 of COA Circular No. 2012-002.

The following courses of actions:
To the Municipal Accountant:
a. Maintain a manual PPE Ledger Cards to record the custody, estimated useful life, depreciation, impairment and disposal of those assets;
To the Municipal General Service Officer:
b. Conduct complete physical count of all LGU properties together with other members of the Inventory Committee of the LGU and report the same using the prescribed RPCPPE form in NGAS Manual for LGUs;
c. Maintain proper and complete records of the PPEs, particularly the stock cards and property cards as stipulated under the NGAS Manual for LGUs, Volume I;
d. Conduct proper procedures to dispose of the unserviceable properties, in coordination with the accounting department to derecognize the same in the books of the agency; and
e. Ensure that any information included in the report presents fair and accurate data that is reliable and verifiable against supporting documents.

To the Municipal Treasurer:
1. Post or record daily transactions in the cashbooks in chronological order and balance and reconciled the same with the actual cash on hand;
2. Cashbooks shall be ruled, footed and closed monthly and shall be certified and the same should be reconciled with the subsidiary/general ledger.
